{{Italic title}}
The '''''Annales Posonienses''''' or '''Annals of Pressburg''' ({{lang-hu|Pozsonyi Évkönyv}}) are the only extant early medieval [[annals]] written in the [[Kingdom of Hungary]].{{sfn|Kristó|1999|p=354}} However, they are rather a collection of notes which, as the historian [[Carlile Aylmer Macartney]] emphasizes, "hardly" deserves "the name of annals".{{sfn|Macartney|1953|p=84}} The annals contain short records of events occurring between 997 and 1203.{{sfn|Kristó|1999|p=354}} They are named after Pressburg (now [[Bratislava]], [[Slovakia]]) where the ''[[Pray Codex]]''{{spaced ndash}}the manuscript preserving its text{{spaced ndash}}was held at [[St. Martin's Cathedral, Bratislava|St. Martin's Cathedral]] until 1813 by the [[collegiate chapter]].{{sfn|Kristó|1999|p=354}}

