'''Claris Organizer''' is a [[personal information management]] (PIM) [[computer program]] for the [[classic Mac OS]] that [[Claris]] acquired from a small company called Trio Development and sold during the 1990s. Trio Development was founded by James Harker, Jack Welde and Joseph Ansanelli,<ref>http://www.ansanelli.com</ref> afterward joined by Seth Odam.  It was sold to [[Palm, Inc.|Palm]] when Claris was broken up, and was used as the basis for the Palm Desktop for Mac.

