{{Infobox software | name = IOzone | logo = <!-- [[File: ]] --> | screenshot = <!-- [[File: ]] --> | caption = | collapsible = | author = William Norcott | developer = Don Capps, et al{{who|date=May 2017}} | released = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | discontinued = | latest release version = 3.465 | latest release date = {{start date and age|2016|08|16}} | latest preview version = | latest preview date = <!-- {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | programming language = [[C (programming language)|C]] | operating system = | platform = | size = | language = English | status = | genre = [[Benchmark (computing)|Benchmark]] | license = | website = {{URL|iozone.org}} }} '''IOzone''' is a file system benchmark utility.<ref>{{cite book | last = Olker | first = Dave | title = Optimizing NFS Performance: Tuning and Troubleshooting NFS on HP-UX Systems | edition = 1st | date = 2002-09-13 | publisher = [[Prentice Hall]] | location = [[Upper Saddle River, New Jersey]] | isbn = 0-13-042816-7 | pages = 24 – 26 | chapter = Local Filesystem Considerations: iozone | quote = iozone is one of the more sophisticated filesystem performance benchmark utilities available. }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.linux.com/archive/feature/139744 | title = IOzone for filesystem performance benchmarking | accessdate = 2009-10-15 | last = Martin | first = Ben | date = 2008-07-03 | publisher = [[Linux.com]] }}</ref> Originally made by William Norcott, further enhanced by Don Capps and others..
Source code is available from iozone.org. It does [[mmap]]() file I/O and uses [[POSIX Threads]].
It won the 2007 [[Infoworld Bossie Awards]] for Best file I/O tool.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.infoworld.com/t/storage/best-open-source-in-storage-139?page=0,1 | title = Best of open source in storage | accessdate = 2009-10-15 | last = Venezia | first = Paul | date = 2007-09-10 | work = 2007 InfoWorld Bossie Awards | publisher = [[InfoWorld]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.infoworld.com/%5Bprimary-term-alias-prefix%5D/%5Bprimary-term%5D/best-open-source-in-storage-837&current=6 | title = Best of open source in storage: slide 6 of 7 | accessdate = 2009-10-15 | date = 2007-09-10 | work = 2007 InfoWorld Bossie Awards | publisher = [[InfoWorld]] }}</ref>
The Windows version of IOzone uses [[Cygwin]]. Builds are available for AIX, BSDI, [[HP-UX]], IRIX, [[FreeBSD]], [[Linux]], [[OpenBSD]], [[NetBSD]], OSFV3, OSFV4, OSFV5, [[SCO OpenServer]], Solaris, [[Mac OS X]], Windows (95/98/Me/NT/2K/XP).
It is available as a test profile in the [[Phoronix Test Suite]].<ref>http://global.phoronix-test-suite.com/?k=category&u=iozone</ref>
